        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 1:37PM EDT by NWS Miami FL</headline>
        <description>At 137 PM EDT, National Weather Service meteorologists were tracking
a strong thunderstorm over Broadview Park, or near Plantation, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 45 to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Lauderdale, Pembroke Pines, Hollywood, Miramar, Coral Springs,
Pompano Beach, Davie, Plantation, Sunrise, Deerfield Beach, Tamarac,
Margate, Lighthouse Point, Lauderdale-By-The-Sea, Hallandale, Miami
Gardens, Lauderhill, North Miami, Coconut Creek, and North Miami
Beach.
</description>
        <instruction>These winds can down small tree limbs and branches, and blow around
unsecured small objects. Seek shelter in a safe building until the
storm passes.</instruction>
